    public interface DynamicMap
extends DynamicValue
    Represents an immutable map that associates Strings with DynamicValues.

      • getProperty

        Collection<DynamicMap.Entry> getProperty(String property)
        Returns a collection of matching mapping for the specified property. Properties are expressed using dot notation.

        Given the following structure, where { a: 5, b: [3, "a", 1.0] } represents a dynamic map with keys "a" and "b", the value of "a" is 5 and the value of "b" is a dynamic list with the items 3, "a" and 1.0: 

         {
     name: "John",
     age: 32,
     score: [ 6, 10, { medal: "gold", points: 10 } ]
 }
        The following entries will be returned for the properties below:

        Property Property key PropertyValue (wrapped in a DynamicValue instance) Note
        name "name" "John"  
        score "score" [ 6, 10, { medal: "gold", points: 10 } ] Returns the array itself
        score.* "score.0" 6 Returns the contents of the array
        "score.1" 10
        "score.2" { medal: "gold", points: 10 }
        score.0 "score.0" 6 Returns a single indexed item
        score.2.medal "score.2.medal" "gold" Returns a subproperty of an indexed item
        score.medal "score.2.medal" "gold" Returns a subproperty for all indexed items that have it

        If there are no matching properties, an empty collection is returned.

        Parameters:
        property - the property to test
        Returns:
        matching entries carrying properties and values

      • propertyContainsList

        boolean propertyContainsList(String property)
        Checks if any of the parts of the specified property chain is associated with a list, with the exception of the last part. If the result is false, the collection returned from getProperty(String) for the same property can have at most one entry.
        Parameters:
        property - the property to test
        Returns:
        true if any part of the property chain corresponds to a list, false otherwise
